review_blob: A very respectable beer with the company name to back it.  It was my first quad belgian style ale and it was a success.  It meet all the requirements and then some, in ordinary Avery style, nothing average about this company.

Wow, Iced coffee meets beer.  Not for the faint of heart, try at your own risk and have food pairing to match this STOUT beer.  It indeed meets the requirements of such a title as so many fall short these days.
A decent pumpkin ale falls short of the pumking by Southern Tier IMO.  A good pumkin palate will leave you satisfied.
beer_name: Heavy Seas Mutiny Fleet The Great Pumpkin

review_blob: A bland pumpkin ale.  Lets consider that it is a seasonal and you may as well go balls out on your creation for the fall, right?  The strong Uinta brand falls short on this one.
A fine seasonal pumpkin ale the lower ABV this year may be a deterrent for some but I think it elevates the richness of this ale.  A very fine pumpkin ale.

The aroma and apperance is expected and the palate is underwhelming.  The roasted malts give this beer the thrust it needs to drive it home as one to remember.  I drank it with the complamentory oatmeal with brown sugar and it was fine.
A thin brown ale that, has a fleeting thin head of white foam, and a translucent brown color for an overall moderate brown ale.
The epitome of brown ale. This is the watermark that I hold all other too.  A must try to for those getting into Brown Ales.

This double IPA has a soft spot in my heart, but doesnt effect the rating in so far as the beer alone is near what a double IPA should be.  Drink this before tasting any other double IPA for benchmarking purposes.
A near perfect stout in my opinion, the head is good looking, with a tast to match the aroma and the gravity to statisfy
